olitical economy approaches to advertising texts in advertising the reception of advertising advertising in the home and outdoor advertising consumer culture. Case studies explore the diversity in the uses of advertising throughout history, from Ostia and the Square of the Corporations in the ancient Roman world to the UK Border Agency's 'Go Home' campaign and contemporary City branding throughout Europe.  Assessing the impact of the works of key critical thinkers including Marx, Morris, Lyotard, Barthes, Saussure, Williams and Hall have had on our understanding of consumption and advertising's societal impact, Advertising: Critical Approaches illuminates and enhances our understanding and engagement with one of the most vital cultural and economic forces in contemporary society. -- Provided by publisher.  a29 0aAdvertising.  aHF5823 .W466 2015hGMCT-OS-Bi1007558958p67.34kAVAIL_SOON1 aCHVBKb3299096141 aCHBISb010163837  aHF5823 .W466 2015wLCc1i1007558958d5/18/2016e2/22/2016lON_SHELFmGR_MACEWANn2p$67.34rYsYtBOOKu4/27/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nb2013020921bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/307438563